    <div class="prose max-w-none text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Getting cited by ChatGPT requires understanding how it decides which sources to reference. ChatGPT cites sources when they provide clear, relevant, and helpful information that answers a user question.

WHAT MAKES CONTENT CITABLE
───────────────────────────
Citable content clearly explains a concept, provides specific examples, and answers questions directly. It is not about having the most content, but having the clearest explanation.

THE 4-STEP CITATION FRAMEWORK
──────────────────────────────
• Define your entity clearly - who you are and what you do
• Answer questions directly - provide clear, specific answers
• Use examples - show real applications of your expertise
• Structure for extraction - make key points easy to find

WHY AUTHORITY HELPS BUT IS NOT REQUIRED
────────────────────────────────────────
ChatGPT considers authority but prioritises helpfulness. A lesser-known source with a better explanation can be cited over a famous brand with vague content.</div>
